args: It went that way, Your Highness!
This is one fast son of a gun...\nTake this!
It's going to escape at this rate!
I thought you folks were taking your\nsweet time coming back. Glad I came\nout to see what was what.
We owe ya one. That thing was too fast\nfor any of us to handle.
So that was the issue, eh?\nWell, glad to have been of help.
The first blade stopped it in its tracks,\nwhile the second was a killing blow.\nThat is truly impressive knifework.
Could someone help me with lunch?
While I appreciate your volunteering,\ncan you actually cook?
You can see that for yourself.\nWhere's the kitchen?
This is some of our circus's famous stew.\nCare to give it a try?
You know how I rollâ€”no matter the\ntarget or the situation, I never miss\nwhat I set my eyes on.
That includes the stomachs of the people\nwho eat my food.
Your cooking certainly backs that up.\nI know the others will love this.
Good. Anything else I can help you with?
Hmm... Might you give me a hand\nbringing in the laundry?
You're very good at this. I expected you to\nat least be surprised at the amount of\nwashing we have to handle.
Feels like being back with the circus,\nactually.
We take turns washing and cooking,\nso I'm pretty used to it.
That explains your earlier stew prowess.
What really needs explaining is your\nworkload. You seem to do everything\naround this place.
Oh, I'm used to it. I've always\nrather liked housework, actually.
Do you two need a hand out here?
Sure, pitch in! The more, the merrier.
I'm not certain how I feel about making\n{player_name} do such work...
Ah! The wind's blowing the laundry away!
I got this. Hah! Ho! Hai!
No! Your daggers are going to... *sigh*
Wow! He stuck all the laundry\nto those trees!
I'm always amazed at just how good your\naim is off-stage as well as on.
Well, I'm always practicing to keep my\nskills sharp.
How's a guy who's always missing in his\noff-time supposed to have flawless aim\nwhen it counts?
So I'm always focused on my accuracy.
Uh oh. That look's scaring me.
Your work ethic and dagger-throwing skills\nare, admittedly, quite impressive.
I'm also glad that you were able to prevent\nthe wind from taking any of our washing.
IT IS NOW FULL OF HOLES!
Just because you can throw daggers does\nnot mean they are the solution to every\nsingle one of life's problems!
Now then! If you have time, I'd like you\nto mend the many, many holes you\nput in our laundry.
You sure? I actually can't sew worth a lick.
But with two of us on it, I suppose it\nwon't take TOO long...
I'm afraid I have to take care of cleaning\nthe castle, so you will be working alone.
The fate of our clothes is in your hands.
It's okay, Fritz. I'll give you a hand.
Lesson learned. Next time I'll just run\naround and catch everything.
